# ── VaultFlow Environment Variables ───────────────────────────────────────────
#
# SETUP:
#   cp .env.local.example .env.local   (Mac/Linux)
#   copy .env.local.example .env.local  (Windows)
#   Then restart the dev server: npm run dev
#
# VaultFlow works out of the box with NO configuration needed.
# The built-in rule-based engine handles all text analysis fully offline.
#
# ── QVAC Local AI (optional) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Set USE_QVAC_SDK=true to enable real on-device LLM inference + image OCR.
#
# What it unlocks:
#   • LLM agent pipeline  — LLAMA_3_2_1B_INST_Q4_0       (~800 MB RAM)
#   • Image / receipt OCR — OCR_0_6B_MULTIMODAL_Q4_K_M   (~500 MB RAM,
#                           loaded on-demand only when you upload an image)
#
# Requirements:
#   • ~1.5 GB free RAM total for both models
#   • First boot downloads & caches models automatically (needs internet once)
#   • GPU (WebGPU) speeds inference up but is NOT required — WASM fallback works
#   • Recommended: 8 GB+ system RAM
#
# If you have less than ~4 GB free RAM, keep this false and paste receipt
# text manually — the rule-based engine categorizes and analyzes it correctly.
#
USE_QVAC_SDK=false
